## Why "same schema" is likely a red herring

Multiple pods sharing one schema doesn't cause connection-reset at the NS layer. If it were a session/connection cap (`SESSIONS_PER_USER`, `processes`), you'd get `ORA-00018`/`ORA-12516`/`ORA-12520` style logon refusals with a message, not a bare TCP reset at `negotiatedOptions=0x0`. The reset-during-negotiation pattern points at transport/TLS, not schema contention.

